caption: Great service great food great beer. Came all the way from the bronx for this
Love this place......RYAN IS MY GUY!!!!!!

Randolph has been around for a while, and a few years ago they upgraded their Williamsburg location to an actual brewpub/brewery. I'm pretty sure they were the first bar in NYC to introduce the pour-your-own-beer concept. A rotating selection of up to 24 beers, both house-made and guest brews, are available by the ounce. They also serve wine, cocktails, and a very solid brunch. Booths by the bar are equipped with a NES mini if you don't feel like talking.
I love the burgers at this place and the Mimosas are Amazing!! Perfect for a date or hang out with friends!!
Great looking interiors, decent service and good food. May be worthwhile going post COVID-19 whenever that will be. Stay safe, wear a mask!
Great time
Good food, good service
The drinks were really good, but the wait was ridiculous. my advice show up early or end up sitting at the bar. But it's worth it..
Best beers in Williamsburg! Food and service is dope as well

I can’t wait to go back when we can sit inside. The service was great and the food was okay (avocado toast was ok, tacos were good but I didn’t love the sauce)  - I would go back to try non-brunch items.  The fry sampler was very very good and huge for the price. The brunch cocktails are also a great price ($18 pitcher of mimosas).

The staff is always friendly and professional. Music is great, the atmosphere virginal, and the drinks delicious. However the food is a bit of a priced for the quality and the drinks are very over priced.

We loved the food, but we ordered a pitcher of mimosas for $18 and got a mini pitcher. It’s pretty deceiving to write on your menu a pitcher, which is usually a standard size and then give people a mini version. It’s way over priced on the drinks.
Love this place. Amazing well thought of retro and modern 80s vibe? Service and food are amazing.

Staff is chill and very down to earth. My order of challah french toast with a side of eggs was great. You can also beer yourself as shown in pic attached to my review!! Definitely recommend if you're in the Williamsburg area.
Menu is short. Cool choices of different beers. Took way too long for the food to come out. You have to sit yourself and then wait forever to even get a menu.
The food is regularly well prepared and flavorful, staff members gives great service. I really like how clean it is and character. Will come back again.

Where do I even begin? When we first arrived the host was incredibly short and stand-offish. There were a couple of open tables but he immediately told us to find our own seats at the bar. When we did find a place to sit it took 20 minutes to get a glass of water and to order anything. We then had to wait another 40 minutes to get our food (which we had to ask again for). The food was mediocre at best. Based upon the service and food we will not be back. There are plenty of other great spots in the area to go to.

Had an absolutely great time, the food was amazing, went for Sunday brunch with a group of my girlfriends... ordered shrimp and grits, cooked to perfection, also got the bottomless mimosas and two other drink choices, the whole meal was great, our hostess gave us the best southern hospitality, definitely planning another visit.

I’d skip it for brunch. Food was served cold, my sandwich was incorrect and bland for the price point I could of got the same thing at the bodega for 5 instead or 14. The only brunch punch worth trying is the Vodka one and even that wasn’t anything to write home about. Our waitress was slow and I and inattentive. Have no want to return.

Heard about this place on INSIDER and this bar became my go to bar when I was living in Brooklyn. Great staff and the beer selection changes every week! Perfect for trying a lot of them without spending too much. Recommend going here for the drinks rather than the food because the food is ridiculously expensive.

Awesome bar! just opened a new side great for hanging out! The assistant manager Mason is great! always right there to help and explain the beer wall process and seems to have a great handle on how this location operates. would always recommend people to come hang out here. Great food, Great drinks and great atmosphere!

Love the Randolph. Really dope concept of pouring your own beer, great atmosphere, and I love the new games section. Everyone working there seems to enjoy their job and know a lot about beer. Assistant manager named Mason is dope, always has great recommendations for food and drinks. Real chiseled guy. Spend a lot of time at the Randolph, and probs won't be going to another bar just so I can wait a million years for a bartender to pour me a single beer any time soon. If you like beer, chill vibes, good vibes and you hate waiting for bartenders, this is the spot for you.
Lots of beer choices, cheap food. Good vibe.
Great food and environment for a Sunday Brunch!
Nice casual brunch in this hip gastropub.
Awesome place for beer and brunch with laid back but helpful service

There are multiple locations to this eatery, allow me to tell you which is the best: ALL of them. We went to Wburg for a birthday brunch and it was cozy as heck. This is usually a nice way to call a place small, but it was beautifully small. They gave complimentary banana nut bread while you wait!? Like hello thank you so much!?! I laid my eyes on fried chicken French tizzle on the menu and knew I had to have it. It was so good I felt like I had just cheated on my girlfriend. Definitely would return
OMG! The best Macaroni & (3) Cheese dish ever! Serving big enough for 2, or 3.
Friendly staff with outdoor seating area that allowed me to sit with my dog. Waitress was very nice and food was delicious.

Though this place seemed nice to the eye at first, it turned out to be be an extreme disappointment. Upon first coming in and sitting down you could off the bat notice the music was blasting unbelievably loud. It was noisy to the point where people where yelling. The waitress put cups on top of cups on top of our table and a water jug and just left it there. Didn’t bother to pour us or offer us any drinks. Then upon ordering the first few appetizers it was already a disappointment. The bread was all stale and the taste of everything .. beyond mediocre. Let’s skip over desert. When finally ordering desert, we wait over 25 minutes for it. During this time our dirty dinner plates are left on the table and we have no more water to drink. The waitress is casually standing outside smoking a cigarette on the job with some of her work friends I guess. Finally the desert comes. Let’s skip to the bill ... $200.00 bill for some apps and dishes. This place is a rowdy bar for young kids who have low quality food standards. The place is loud. The food is very mediocre and the service is terrible. I can’t even recommend anything on the menu. An overall disappointment.
Amazing wings and always a superb tap selection. Also has some cool bar games (free pinball, etc)
I had the steak sandwich and it was to die for! Cool place to hang out. Music isnt too loud so you can hear the conversation your having.
Great beer selection and cool machine. Food was poor

Slow service, servers wandering away from the restaurant to chat with friends and overpriced beer. Food was okay. Would not recommend, would not go back. The auto dispensing beer is nice if you are the only one there. You can take your time, read descriptions, taste a variety. But in any other state of people waiting for beer, it's a pretty poor system. Not to mention the $12 drafts.
Great food and service! The beer wall is a fun concept that lets people try new beers or stick with their favorite.

Honestly, I just went in to see the hockey game on the big screen. The service was extremely nice and knowledgeable. I tried some beers I didn't know and the expertise impressed me a lot. Found a new favorite of US beer. The highlight of the evening was a free ice cream sandwich on the house. I will definitely come back. Even without getting something for free. What makes this location unique is the staff, they love to host.
Nice bar with cool atmosphere. I really enjoyed the beer wall that had over a dozen beers on tap. It’s a unique concept, and with a great weekday happy hour, it’s very reasonable pricing.
Credit card only is different but cool. Self serve beer is great as well. Stopped during bar crawl, nice little chill spot.

If you’re looking for a bottomless brunch spot that offers clean food and quality cocktails, look no more! They’ve got ‘beer buffet’ option that let’s to choose the beers on tap(10-12 beer taps) for a price. Food was delicious as well and the service was great!  Highly recommend the fried chicken sandwich option with a Saison beer to pair with it. Their menu offers your traditional run home menu options with suggestions on beer pairings.  We will definitely be back!

I love the beer self-serv. You ever just stare at a beer menu trying to find the perfect beer ? Now you can try an ounce of each. I feel like a kid again at the soda dispenser machine. The food is pretty friggin good too.

if you are a cider drinker, they have 2 kinds

We made a reservation for bottomless brunch. We arrived a little early, and we were seated right away. It's not too crowded, and the music is not too loud. This has to be the best bottomless place in NY. It works out to be $37 in total (Bottomless for 90 mins plus a $17 entree).. Absolutely worth the money. Their drinks are powerful, have a good punch and they are very generous about the way they serve it. They literally put the pitcher of drinks on your table and let you have a good time. The servers are extremely attentive, thanks a lot Britney! We had an amazing time here and this will definitely be one of our favorite brunch places in Williamsburg! Hope they keep up this excellent service! Reservations highly recommended for large groups.

I really enjoyed the first two times I was here, but last night was horrible. I love that I get to try various beers, have however much I want, and pour my own cup and the food is pretty good too (when it gets to you!) However, last night was just pure incompetency. At least four of the beers on the self-pour wall kicked as we were pouring, so we were charged for mostly head, which is fine, but at least change the keg or turn it off, so it doesn't keep happening to others. We told the servers/bartenders multiple times and it was clear that they didn't really care. Next we ordered a pretzel, got the first one, and when we wanted to order another, we ordered at the bar (where we placed the first order), he said ok, and then never got it after 20 minutes. Checked with the same server and he said we were supposed to order with the girl, who was serving other tables, but had never came to us even once. Tried to place the order with her and then she said we had voided it...what?! We were just fed up by then and just wanted to go, and saw the kitchen guys leaving anyway. The servers looked they were trying to close anyway as well, but it was only midnight on a Friday! They comp'd the one pretzel...yay. But never again!
Food wasn't great but the bottomless mimosas and rum punch is well worth a visit. We spent 5 hours chatting and having an amazing time last Saturday morning.
Fun space, a bit loud. The brunch is amazing. Waffle fries , avocado toast , shishito peppers and beer ATM.

And awesome bar where everything is on tap and one can drink as much or as little of each beer type they like. Payments are made by the ounce and vary depending on which beer is being dispensed. Definitely recommend and will definitely be back!
